\left(-\frac{b}{2a}, p(-\frac{b}{2a})\right)
p(x) = ax^2+bx+c
(-\frac{b}{2a},c)
c \ge -\frac{1}{4a}
(x-(-\frac{b}{2a}))^2=\frac{1}{a}(y-\frac{4ac-b^2}{4a})
-\frac{b}{2a},\frac{4ac-b^2}{4a}
x=y
-\frac{b}{2a}=-\frac{b^2-4ac}{4a}\implies 4ac=b^2-2b=(b-1)^2-1≥-1
b
\implies 4ac≥-1\implies c≥-\frac{1}{4a}
a>0
